  "text": "An age-related association between the HLA class II susceptibility haplotypes DRB1*04-DQB1*0302 (DR4-DQ8) and DRB1*03-DQB1*0201 (DR3-DQ2) and type 1 diabetes in the general population is well established, with an increased frequency in young children with type 1 diabetes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . These haplotypes also appear to contribute to susceptibility to diabetes in DS, but to a lesser degree [CITATION_3] .",
